Next thing to do

Let's first make sure deletion is allowed.

Check:

oc get noobaa noobaa -n openshift-storage -o yaml | grep -A10 cleanupPolicy

Then patch with the correct fields:

oc patch noobaa noobaa -n openshift-storage \
--type=merge \
-p '{
  "spec":{
    "cleanupPolicy":{
      "allowNoobaaDeletion": true,
      "confirmation": "yes-really-delete-noobaa"
    }
  }
}'

Verify again:

oc get noobaa noobaa -o yaml -n openshift-storage | grep -A10 cleanupPolicy

You should see:

cleanupPolicy:
  allowNoobaaDeletion: true
  confirmation: yes-really-delete-noobaa


---

If patch still does not take

Then let's inspect the CRD schema because ODF 4.18 sometimes validates the exact confirmation string.

Run:

oc get crd noobaas.noobaa.io -o yaml | grep -A20 cleanupPolicy

and paste the output.

At this point I would not attempt SQL fixes. The database has no system records at all, which means rebuilding NooBaa is much safer than manually reconstructing metadata tables. The goal now is to get NooBaa deleted cleanly so ODF can recreate it from scratch.
